While Boomer and Sheba pursue Apollo, Iblis frees the colonial prisoners and arms them to destroy the colony of New Eden City. The Nomen take over the Galactica and prepare to execute the council. Iblis tries to convince Apollo to help him defeat Adam and Eve.
name: Battlestar Galactica: Apollo's Journey #2

description: Apollo uses the power of Adam's amulet to focus his personal power against Iblis and the Nomen. Baltar resents the Imperious Leader taking control of the attack, so he transmits the wrong attack coordinates to the Cylon fleet.
name: Battlestar Galactica: Apollo's Journey #3

description: Apollo and crew try to unravel the puzzle of the Pyramid, the Council of Twelve ( Tigh is now president) declare that it is time to execute Adama's last command - to revive Adama from stasis if Earth is found. Count Iblis and Baltar come along to cause trouble.
name: War of Eden (part 2 of 4)

description: Adama and crew gain entrance to the pyramid. Baltar pursues the humans using a warp corridor generator appropriated from the Unari. Count Iblis tricks Sheba into believing Apollo knew her father, Cain, was dead and did not tell her.
name: War of Eden (part 3 of 4)

description: Baltar's fleet attacks the humans. Sheba shoots Apollo. The Seraphs save the day by bringing the Battlestar Pegasus and Commander Cain across to Earth. Adama dies.
name: War of Eden (part 4 of 4)

description: A seraph named Elias appears to Apollo to warn him of the coming of nearly 100 Cylon base ships. Apollo says flee. Cain says stay and fight. Adam and Eve cannot leave. When the Cylons attack, Elias transports the Galactica away into the future. The missing Starbuck goes day by day stranded on a remote planet.
name: Journey's End (part 1 of 4)

description: During a battle between East Alliance Destroyers and the Galactica, Starbuck's fighter is damaged and he is forced to land on the Lunar One prison colony. Discovered by Western Nationalist's, Starbuck agree's to help them free the Nationlist, Joseph.
name: Officer's Club..the Battlestar Galactica

description: A colonial craft is disabled by Cylons, but then rescued by mysterious orbs of light - the Seraphs. On the planet Arilos, a young boy named Adama finds an old Cylon head and meets a crazy man.
name: Battlestar Galactica: Special Edition #1

description: The crew of the Galactica find a strange vessel that contains a possible survivor from the thirteenth tribe.
name: The Enemy Within

description: When gods go to war! A new epic ongoing exploring Lovecraft's Cthulhu Mythos. The 1928 publication of The Call of Cthulhu established one of the most feared characters in the history of horror fiction: a terrible alien god capable of worldwide destruction. But Cthulhu was actually only one of the minor gods in Lovecraft's pantheon - there are things far bigger, badder, and meaner roaming the cosmos, ready to come to call.

description:
Riddler starts his own riddle show. That isn't good...
In this issue the Riddler has a new public access TV show where he humiliates and exposes the secrets of the rich, all the while giving his audience a chance to win money or experience pai, depending on wether they answer it correctly or not.
Batman and Gordon are on the case, especially when they find out that on his next show, the Riddler wants to expose the secrets of Billionare Bruce Wayne.
name: Batman: Riddler and the Riddle Factory

volume.name: Batman: Riddler and the Riddle Factory

description: Boba Fett is hired by Darth Vader to retrieve a box, upon the success of Fett's mission he discovers that Vader doesn't want to risk Fett having knowledge of the box's contents, as they may hold the key to the galaxy itself, and Fett now finds himself a fugitive from the Galactic Empire. Set before Star Wars: A New Hope.
name: TPB

volume.name: Star Wars: Boba Fett - Enemy of the Empire

description: From the writer that Rue Morgue Magazine called "The next Brian K. Vaughn or Robert Kirkman"! Forces are moving in the cosmos. Mankind is on the verge of facing alien beings far beyond its kin. Is another call for Cthulhu just starting to begin? Human innocents are caught in the middle and not prepared for the real truth - which will drive them to the brink of insanity. What happens in a world of Lovecraftian darkness when a god is fated to die? What things are more vast than the Elder Gods?
name: The Fugue, Part 1 of 5: Harlot

description: A series of stunning revelations leads to the discovery that the Call of Cthulhu just might be happening - again. And yet, there are greater forces at work in Lovecraft's universe, forces that do not even recognize the existence of man. Facing an abyss of darkness and insanity, is there a greater call than Cthulhu's? The earth-spanning horror epic continues with new, startling revelations that just might lead you to believe that a god can die.
name: The Fugue, Part 2 of 5: The Black Chorus

description: Lovecraftian horror in the present day, with a decidedly different bend. Now that Cy has become persuaded that the Call of Cthulhu is happening, what is standing in its way? And how is it Cthulhu's very followers who are the greatest barrier to his rising? Other forces in Lovecraft's universe array against these tidal movements, and Cy soon discovers that he has been pulled into an abyss of despair and powers far beyond the mortal.
name: The Fugue, Part 3 of 5: The Hunt

description: Cy's entire world has been turned upside-down by the death of his uncle. Things are starting to unravel, as his nightmares intensify - he's traveling to the Dreamlands, and seeing horrific visions. What secrets does that land hold, and what are its connections to what he's enduring on earth? Meanwhile, is the cult of Cthulhu calling their master? Or wrapped up in something else?
name: The Fugue, Part 4 of 5: Lucky

description:
Cy is pulled further into the world of darkness. As he descends into Lovecraftian madness, the pull and the tug of the alternate dimension known only as The Dreamlands gets stronger. Is Cy strong enough to avoid destruction? Can he resist the pull of insanity?

And what does this mean for his life and his world, with his girlfriend Jordan? Will he ever be safe?
name: The Fugue, Part 5 of 5: The Conductor

description: Lightning Lad and Saturn Girl get married and the Legion of Super-Heroes and the Legion of Substitute Heroes are invited. Superboy flies into the future to attend the wedding when he notices the future is distinctly different from what he recalled: the Metropolis of the future is unusually militaristic. Projectra explains that in 1978, the United Nations disbanded and humans made more dangerous weapons than atomic bombs to fight against each other, and that resentment continued to gain momentum into the future, where Earth is at war with Venus, who is at war with Winath, and so on. Superboy realizes he has to fix the time stream and demands an emergency meeting after the wedding, but as soon as the wedding is over, Saturn Girl and Lightning Lad are kidnapped by galactic invaders. While most of the Legion want to give chase to return the newly-married couple, Superboy insists that going into the past would solve everything. While the one team of Legionnaires are able to save Lightning Lad and Saturn Girl before they die, Superboy and his team find the real culprit behind the time disruption: the Time Trapper. The Legion of Super-Heroes are able to use the Miracle Machine top stop the Time Trapper's menace and they succeed, reverting reality to its true form.
name: Superboy and the Legion of Super Heroes: The Millenium Massacre

description: Our first series of Jungle Girl adventures nears its a smashing conclusion with a closing on its way that is going to be talked about for years to come! More secrets of the island and its cast-away's are revealed as it all counts down to the end, or is it?

Our first series of Jungle Girl adventures comes to a smashing conclusion with a closing that is going to be talked about for years to come! More secrets of the island and its cast-aways are revealed as it all counts down to the end, or is it?

Although Eva made her debut in the Army Of Darkness story arc Ash vs. The Monsters, writer Brandon Jerwa and artist Edgar Salazar decided it was time to give her more importance in order to develop her strong character and in Eva: Daughter of the Dragon, she will have to face her father, Dracula.
name: Eva: Daughter of the Dragon

description:
Bart's life appears to be ruined when Mrs. Krabappel moves in with the Simpsons. Then, Homer and Bart go head to head and burger to burger when they both enter a Krusty Burger competition. Finally, Bart discovers Groundskeeper Willie's infamous past.

1. Fort Knocks (written by Tony Digerolamo)

Can Bart and Milhouse find a fort?

2. The Uter Bomber (written by Mary Trainor)

Bart + Uter + See Saw + Balloons = Splash!

3. A Load of Trouble (starring Lisa Simpson / written by Tony Digerolamo)

Lisa's laundry doesn't come out as expected

4. Signs of Intelligent Life (written by Clay and Susan Griffith)

When an alien visitor comes to town, Bart teaches him how to prank.
name: Large & in Charge

description:
Tokyo. The cultural and economic hub of the Eastern world. Not unlike the legendary city of Babylon, its man-made tower stretches toward the heavens... a symbol of its people's ambition and their indomitable spirit. Nowhere on Earth will you find such vanity... or such beauty.

This is my home.

My name is Sumeragi Subaru, and I hunt the dead. Then I return them to peace.

No matter where my work leads me, I suspect I'll never leave Tokyo in spirit. But then again, it seems so few people do these days...
name: Volume 1

description:
'CRESCENDO' Four hundred years is a long time time to wait for anything, but Chinatsu's quest may finally be about to come to an end. The vampire she has been stalking is now in New York and seeks an audience with her. What are his intentions? Has he grown tired of the chase? Will Chinatsu be willing to settle for anything less than his death?!

SPOILERS

Chinatsu's epic revenge is finally coming to an end and where it all began. Sorrounded by the souls of those she loved the most, Chinatsu and Reiji confront for the last time and only one will walk away alive.
name: Crescendo

description:
Overview

A new two-part story begins as one of the Sith's most wily opponents risks everything to gain ground against the Empire!

For seven years, outlaw Admiral Gar Stazi has led the remains of the Galactic Alliance in hit-and-run operations against the Sith-led Empire. When word reaches him of a nearly completed, top-secret Imperial construction, he gambles his entire fleet to seize the project and turn the tide of war against the Sith!

Last Stand of the Galactic Alliance!
name: Indomitable, Part One

description:
Overview

The conclusion of a shocking two-part tale pitting the Sith Empire against the Galactic Alliance in an all-out space battle!

The Sith have lured outlaw Admiral Gar Stazi into a trap to destroy the Alliance once and for all. Yet Stazi is no fool-he may have agreed to play the Sith's game, but not with the cards they expect! Meanwhile, forces loyal to the deposed Emperor Roan Fel wait on the sidelines. Are they here to help, to hurt, or simply make off with whatever's left when the dust settles?

Stazi springs the Empire's trap!
name: Indomitable, Part Two

description:
Spider-Man, Storm, and Power Man help a young track runner stop smoking and defeat a villain named Smokescreen. Smokescreen is trying to get athletes hooked on smoking, then betting against them, knowing that their smoking will prevent them from winning any meets.

This is a free promotional book given to children by the American Cancer Society to help raise awareness about the dangers of smoking.

No credits are given for story or artwork.

description: Rachel begins to teach Raymond to control the Breed power.
Raymond learns his mother is still alive.
Raymond and Rachel are discovered by the Demons. A pack of Breed are dispatched to kill them.
Rachel dies. Continued in Breed II mini-series.

After three years of hiding in a Monastery in Tibet, Ray Stoner still cannot embrace the Monster that lies within him.

Haunted by his past and fearful for his future, and knowing that peace can never be his, Ray once again enters the world only to be attacked by his brethren, fellow 'Breed warriors.

But what chance can any 'Breed have when facing "The Prodigal"?

Perhaps Ray can hide from his Destiny in Honduras, but I wouldn't count on it! There are more than just 'Breed after him, there is also the C.I.A.!

description:
The travelers are prevented by their code from supporting a culture that harms its own planet, or from encouraging individual paths that keep the species or civilization from its ow destiny. Nor will they promote the good of the society above that of the individual. The only goal is "The Balance of Three" - Trivolution - the interlocking evolution of the individual, the civilization s/he lives in and the natural environment.

Central to the theme of "help" in the travelers code is the knowledge that one cannot help an individual without helping a species; that one cannot help a species without helping the environment of the species.
name: Payeru Attack

description:
The Deliverance has maintained orbit over the planet Malay for thirty-six hours while an advance team led by Commander Penaltra Blue has arrived on the surface in pursuit of Mission Scientist, Dr. Alexander Grange. Onboard homing beacons have been activated for use by the other Plan*Net vessels, and the Hercules. A Plan*Net long-range freighter, has been ordered to standby for possible support of the Malay Mission Team.

The second photo is the flipside cover for this issue.
